examples.en: Day by day he grew weaker.
A weaker person would have buckled under the weight of criticism.
Teachers have been given instructions to mark up the weaker students.
If food is scarce, the mother will feed the smaller, weaker chicks.
The military machine is the same one we faced in 1991 but now it is weaker.
It is one of the lessons of history that more powerful civilizations often subordinate weaker ones.
Marxism has never been weaker as a political creed.
